A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending the American Legion Post 105; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the American Legion was chartered by Congress in 1919 as a patriotic,
3 mutual-help, war-time veterans organization, and it has since grown into a distinguished
4 community-service organization with nearly 3 million members in over 15,000 posts
5 worldwide; and
6 WHEREAS, chartered on September 20, 1927, by 19 World War I veterans, Fayette County
7 Post 105 has upheld a proud legacy of service, with its members contributing to all major
8 conflicts and continuously supporting the communities of Fayette County and the State of
9 Georgia; and
10 WHEREAS, Fayette County Post 105 has met at the historic Log Cabin in Fayetteville,
11 Georgia, since 1936, which was constructed through the Works Progress Administration as
12 part of President Franklin D. Roosevelt's New Deal program to provide employment during
13 the Great Depression; and
14 WHEREAS, in recognition of Women's History Month, Fayette County Post 105 has
15 demonstrated outstanding leadership by hosting a Post Dinner and Meeting to honor military
