16 women veterans, acknowledging their sacrifice, service, and the vital role they have played
17 in the United States Armed Forces; and
18 WHEREAS, military women veterans have exhibited extraordinary bravery, discipline, and
19 selflessness in service to the nation, paving the way for future generations of women while
20 preserving the freedoms and values held dear by the American people; and
21 WHEREAS, Fayette County Post 105's unwavering dedication to veterans, its commitment
22 to community service, and its efforts to honor and uplift military women veterans during
23 Women's History Month exemplify the highest ideals of the American Legion.
24 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
25 recognize and commend the American Legion Post 105 for its service, leadership, and
26 dedication to veterans and the community and extend best wishes for continued success.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
28 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the American
29 Legion Post 105.
